text_Basalt: Sandy-like surface with holes that formed due to lava flows and cooling. Not as many or any holes in surface.
text_Pumice: Sandy-like surface which looks more like a sponge type. Usually has more holes than basalts.

text_Diorite: Are speckled in appearance with mostly a black and white pattern.
text_Gabbro: More of a dull appearance considered igneous type.

text_Andesite: Dull appearance of igneous type. Filled with other quartz type fragments.
text_Peridotite: Sandy/rough texture of igneous type. Has more of a shiny appearance than andesite.

text_Andesite: Igneous type rock with fragmets of quartz type rock inside.
text_Peridotite: Rougher surface of igneous type. Fragments of shiny quartz type rock and some smaller holes that seem similar to pumice type

text_Basalt: Darker texture with sandy-like surface. Igneous type with some holes in surface.
text_Pumice: Lighter texture with many holes in surface. Igneous type with rough surface.

text_Diorite: Lighter color with more of a speckling/dalmatian type look.
text_Gabbro: Igneous type with rough/darker surface. Some speckling but not much.
